locality: South Africa, Free State, one km east of Maselpoort Resort, next to Modder River. Gentle hill slope, in shallow soil on sandstone banks, in full sun. Well-drained rocky soil of sandstone loam. Native and common, pasture along roadside. Grassland with Euryops empetrifolius, Nenax microphylla, Aristida congesta, Eragrostis lehmanniana, Acacia karroo and Rhus pyroides. Perennial succulent, 5 cm high, spreading 5-20 cm across, roots somewhat fleshy. Leaves alternate, simple, glabrous, leaf margins entire. Solitary flowers yellow, open during afternoon, close in the night. Fruit a capsule.
Peckerwood Garden: outside of art gallery.
